usage: scanner.py [-h] [-p PORTS] [-t THREADS] [-T TIMEOUT] target
Fast & Clean TCP Port Scanner
positional arguments:
  target                Target IP address or hostname
options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -p, --ports PORTS     Port range to scan (default: 1-1000)
  -t, --threads THREADS
                        Number of concurrent threads (default: 200)
  -T, --timeout TIMEOUT
                        Connection timeout in seconds (default: 1.0)

Example: 
OS- CentOS Stream 9 [root user]

sudo dnf install python3-pip -y
git clone https://github.com/NJc-24/Port-Scanner.git
cd Port-Scanner/
pip install pyfiglet

python3 scanner.py [target-IP/domain] -p [target-ports] -t [threads]
